<DOC><DOCNO> AP880811-0104 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-11-88 1204EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-FatalFall     08-11 0224</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Fatal Fall,0229</SECOND><HEAD>Man Killed In Fall From Amusement Park Ride</HEAD><DATELINE>OMAHA, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A man died of head injuries today afterfalling 15 feet from a whirling amusement park ride, police said.   Witnesses reported that the man appeared to be clowning aroundand was not secured by the safety bar Wednesday night, said BillRamsey, a Peony Park spokesman.   Byron James Conant, 31, of Missouri Valley, Iowa, died atMethodist Hospital after the fall from the Hurricane, which has sixtwo-seat cars extended on arms that rotate and move up and downabout a center shaft.   Police Sgt. Mike Cavanaugh said Conant was in the front seat ofa car with a friend in the back. He said the operator noticedConant in an unsafe position about 20 seconds into the ride but wasunable to stop the ride before the man fell.   Witnesses told officers Conant appeared to be kneeling outside asafety bar or turning around to talk to his friend, Cavanaugh said.He said the bar appeared to be operating properly, but he orderedthe ride closed for further investigation.   Ramsey said the park has operated the Hurricane for severalyears without accident. The last serious accident at the parkoccurred about 12 years ago when a person died on a ride that laterwas removed, he said.</TEXT></DOC>